Preconditions:
- The method takes three parameters: an integer `n`, a 2D integer array `edges`, and an integer array `queries`.
- The length of the `answers` array should be equal to the length of the `queries` array.

Postconditions:
- The method returns an integer array `answers`.
- The length of the `answers` array is equal to the length of the `queries` array.
- Each element `answers[j]` in the `answers` array is the answer to the `j`th query.